# 6. 役者と演出家

Doggie Plushie: C'mon! I can do better than this!
Kitty Plushie: No, it's too dangerous...!
KAITO: I see... So that's what brought you here.
Rui: Yes. I'm at a loss as to what to do.
Rui: I'm not consciously holding back or anything either...
KAITO: Holding back...? Has this ever happened before?
Rui: No, not really.
Rui: If anything, I've always done the opposite.
Little Rui: And for the finale, we'll all jump down from the wall. How does that sound?
Friend A: It does sound fun... But it also seems a little dangerous.
Friend B: I don't want to end up getting hurt or anything...
Little Rui: But it's going to be fun...! Everyone watching will love it and we can even place a trampoline for us to land on!
Friend A: Ask someone else. I'm not doing it.
Friend B: Me neither. If I get hurt, my mom will get so mad at me.
Little Rui: Oh...
KAITO: That paints a vivid picture...
Rui: There were a few kids who would get excited about my ideas.
Rui: But sooner or later, even they became fed up with me.
Rui: It kept happening again and again. Eventually there was no one left that wanted anything to do with me.
Nene: ...
Junior High School Nene: Rui...
Junior High School Rui: Oh, Nene. It's been a while...
Junior High School Rui: I heard you're going to be the lead for a show. Congratulations!
Junior High School Nene: Oh, yeah. Thanks.
Junior High School Nene: And, um... How are you...?
Junior High School Rui: I'm working on a solo project... But I haven't found anyone else like you that's willing to help.
Junior High School Nene: Oh, I see...
Junior High School Nene: Then would you like to join the troupe I'm in...?
Junior High School Nene: I mean, uh...
Junior High School Rui: Hehe. It's nice of you to invite me, but there's no need to pity me. I'm doing okay on my own, and it's for the best anyway.
Junior High School Rui: I've got to go. I still have plenty of work left for my show. Good luck with yours, Nene.
Junior High School Nene: R-Rui...
Nene: I know you're actually very considerate of others. I know this for a fact...
Nene: Your ideas sometimes sound crazy, but you take steps to make sure they're safe.
Nene: As long as they trust you and follow your instructions, they'll be fine. I know this because we used to try your ideas when we were little.
Rui: Hehe. Thank you, Nene.
Rui: These shows mean everything to me. Nothing makes me happier than seeing you, Tsukasa and Emu having fun while bringing what I wrote to life.
Rui: That's why the thought that I'm holding back doesn't make sense to me.
KAITO: Yes, I understand.
KAITO: Rui, you feel like you've found a place where you belong.
Rui: Huh?
KAITO: You finally found a group of friends who let you unleash your full potential. Isn't this how you feel?
Rui: Well...
Tsukasa: But you need to challenge yourself to make extraordinary performances! And I aim to be the world's greatest star!
Tsukasa: If it's for the sake of entertaining my audience, I'll pull off even the most dangerous stunts with elegance and grace!
Tsukasa: If it's to put on a good show, then I'll do anything!
Tsukasa: Aaargh!!
Rui: ...!!
Rui: ...
KAITO: It looks like you've figured it out.
Rui: Yes... It started with that accident.
Rui: On a subconscious level, I must have been so afraid that Tsukasa would start hating me and leave, like everyone else did...
Rui: Somewhere along the way, I started to press the brakes out of not wanting to lose what took me so long to find...
Rui: I'm honestly surprised. This never occurred to me...
Rui: Hehe...
Rui: I disappointed my friends, who are working so hard, over these fears. I let them down as their director...
KAITO: Rui, your concerns are nothing to be ashamed of.
KAITO: I'd like you lot to hear about this too.
Plushies: Us?
KAITO: You genuinely love these shows, so it's only natural that you'd want to preserve this place you've found.
KAITO: Of course, nobody wants to see their friends get hurt in the process.
KAITO: But you all share the same goal of wanting to put on great shows that will delight your audience.
KAITO: Which is why it becomes important to find a balance, so that you can all move ahead together.
KAITO: I'm sure Tsukasa will understand where you are coming from.
Nene: I think so too...
Nene: We can find a way to work things out. I'm sure Tsukasa will come around too.
Nene: He's kind of a nutcase. A show maniac if that even makes sense.
Nene: But I mean... You're one too, right?
Nene: I doubt he'll turn his back on you like this.
Rui: Hehe... I really have found something special.
Rui: Which is why I need to make sure you guys can count on me.
Emu: Tsukasaaa! Calm down already...! ...Bwargh!
Emu: Ugh... Don't stop so suddenly like that...!
Tsukasa: Emu, please tell me....
Emu: Hm?
Tsukasa: Do you think Rui's shows are good?
Emu: Yeah! I LOVE them!
Emu: They remind me of Grandpa's shows!
Emu: Like they're super exciting from start to finish, and make you feel all fuzzy inside!
Tsukasa: Exactly, I like that about them too.
Tsukasa: And that's why I got so angry...
Tsukasa: The four of us teamed up to create shows that are fun for everyone, but it was like Rui forgot what we were trying to achieve...
Tsukasa: Well, it's not entirely his fault...
Tsukasa: If that accident never happened, Rui wouldn't be like this now.
Emu: Huh...?
Emu: You mean you weren't just mad at Rui? You were mad at yourself too?
Tsukasa: Of course! I still am too! I killed the director's confidence, didn't I? I'm not a star, I'm a disgrace!
Tsukasa: A real star inspires their director to entrust them with any role! To unleash their imagination and try new ideas!
Emu: Hehe♪ There's the Tsukasa we all know and love!
Tsukasa: Hm?
Tsukasa: Anyway, this is what I'm going to tell Rui tomorrow. The last time we spoke, I was at a loss for words...
Emu: Yeah! I'm sure he'll hear you out!
